        div(class='row row-cols-1 row-cols-xl-2')

            div(class='col mb-4')
                div(class='card h-100')
                    div(class='card-header') Greensboro Science Center and SkyWild
                    ul(class='list-group list-group-flush')
                        li(class='list-group-item') 01:00 PM - 05:00 PM Saturday, February 08, 2020
                        li(class='list-group-item')
                            a(href='https://goo.gl/maps/U6jkkdVopNKeFZwz6') 4301 Lawndale Drive, Greensboro, NC 27455
                        li(class='list-group-item') General Pre-Registration: $14.00. Closes on Friday, February 7th, 2020 at 11:59 PM.
                        li(class='list-group-item') SKYWILD Pre-Registration: $42.00. Closes Saturday, February 1st, 2020 at 11:59 PM.
                        li(class='list-group-item') General On-site Registration: [insert on-site price].
                    div(class='card-body')
                        div(class='container')
                            div(class='row row-cols-1 row-cols-md-2')
                                div(class='col text-center mb-4')
                                    a(class='btn btn-lg btn-outline-primary' href='/events/greensboro-science-center.html') More Information
                                div(class='col text-center mb-4')
                                    a(class='btn btn-lg btn-outline-primary' href='') Register Now
                        p(class='card-text')
                            | Join NCAS as we tour the Greensboro Science Center on February 8th, 2020! In addition to
                            | the awesome museum, the science center offers both an aquarium and a zoo! If you’re
                            | feeling adventurous, the treetop adventure park SKYWILD will have you climbing, flying,
                            | and sliding through the trees.
                        p(class='card-text')
                            | Please note that SKYWILD registration includes general
                            | registration. SKYWILD registration is only available during pre-registration.

            div(class='col mb-4')
                div(class='card h-100')
                    div(class='card-header') Something for Dogbomb - Raleigh ALS Walk Kickoff!
                    ul(class='list-group list-group-flush')
                        li(class='list-group-item') 06:30 PM - 08:30 PM Thursday, February 27, 2020.
                        li(class='list-group-item')
                            a(href='https://goo.gl/maps/8GbHNtoYBs7apVHB7') Stalls Medical Cary 7980 Chapel Hill Rd, Cary NC 27513
                    div(class='card-body')
                        div(class='container')
                            div(class='row row-cols-1 row-cols-md-2')
                                div(class='col text-center mb-4')
                                    a(class='btn btn-lg btn-outline-primary' href='/events/als-walk.html') More Information
                                div(class='col text-center mb-4')
                                    a(class='btn btn-lg btn-outline-primary' href='https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1WQ7S1_dMeJDydqsdP9hRaluL_nfg0wDGqiZnmqvecbg/edit?usp=sharing') Kickoff Registration
                            div(class='row row-cols-1')
                                div(class='col text-center mb-4')
                                    a(class='btn btn-lg btn-outline-primary' href='http://webnc.alsa.org/goto/friendsoftony') Fundraiser Registration
                        p(class='card-text')
                            | The ALS Walk kickoff is a warm up gathering hosted by the ALS Association focused on
                            | sponsors, long time contributors, volunteers, care givers, and more. Come join the
                            | #[a(href='http://webnc.alsa.org/goto/friendsoftony') Friends of Tony], meet your fellow
                            | teammates, interact with other teams, and learn about new research and treatment
                            | development in the fight to kick ALS in the butt.
                        p(class='card-text')
                            | Food and beverages will be provided. Registration is required so that the ALS Association
                            | can plan accordingly. Registration is free!

            div(class='col mb-4')
                div(class='card h-100')
                    div(class='card-header') Something for Dogbomb - Raleigh ALS Walk
                    ul(class='list-group list-group-flush')
                        li(class='list-group-item') 08:30 AM Saturday, April 18, 2020.
                        li(class='list-group-item')
                            a(href='https://goo.gl/maps/cgiZwsQiUvLWYrAw8') Halifax Mall, 300 N Salisbury St, Raleigh, NC 27601
                    div(class='card-body')
                        div(class='container')
                            div(class='row row-cols-1 row-cols-md-2')
                                div(class='col text-center mb-4')
                                    a(class='btn btn-lg btn-outline-primary' href='/events/als-walk.html') More Information
                                div(class='col text-center mb-4')
                                    a(class='btn btn-lg btn-outline-primary' href='https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/17WMiz7VWlb6GrhvojIe7AANUFnSTR0H0uD2A-G6sEBU/edit?usp=sharing') Walk Registration
                            div(class='row row-cols-1')
                                div(class='col text-center mb-4')
                                    a(class='btn btn-lg btn-outline-primary' href='http://webnc.alsa.org/goto/friendsoftony') Fundraiser Registration
                        p(class='card-text')
                            | #[a(href='http://webnc.alsa.org/goto/friendsoftony') Friends of Tony] is a team formed in
                            | support and honor of Tony “Dogbomb” Barrett, a member of the anthropomorphic community
                            | who was diagnosed with Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis (ALS).
                        p(class='card-text')
                            | ALS is a progressive neurodegenerative disease that affects nerves in the brain and spinal
                            | cord. It slowly robs the body of its ability to walk, speak, swallow, and breathe. The
                            | life expectancy of a person with ALS averages 2 to 5 years from the time of diagnosis. The
                            | Friends of Tony  are dedicated to aiding the ALS association in their goal of bringing
                            | hope, raising awareness, and providing resources and services to families affected by ALS
                            | free of charge.
                        p(class='card-text')
                            | Join the Friends of Tony as they walk in memory of Dobgomb on April 18, 2020 at the
                            | Raleigh ALS Walk hosted by the ALS Association. Check-in is at 08:30 AM, and the walk
                            | starts at 10:00 AM. The walk length is 2 miles. Fursuits are very much welcome!

